  <header>
    <h1>What is the Salary Range for TOSCA Automation Engineers?</h1>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>
      TOSCA automation engineers are responsible for designing, executing, and maintaining automated test scripts using the Tricentis TOSCA platform. Due to the increasing demand for skilled automation testers, their salaries vary depending on experience, location, and expertise.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Salary Range</h2>
    <p>
      On average, entry-level TOSCA automation engineers can expect a salary ranging from <strong>$50,000 to $70,000 per year</strong>, while mid-level professionals may earn between <strong>$70,000 to $90,000 per year</strong>. Senior-level engineers or those with specialized skills in complex automation scenarios can command salaries exceeding <strong>$100,000 per year</strong>.
    </p>
    <p>
      Geographic location, industry, and certification status also significantly influence compensation. Professionals with recognized credentials like a <a href="https://www.h2kinfosys.com/courses/tosca-automation-tool-training-and-certification-program/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">TOSCA Training</a> often see higher salary prospects and faster career growth.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Factors Affecting Salary</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Years of experience in automation testing.</li>
      <li>Industry vertical (finance, healthcare, IT services, etc.).</li>
      <li>Proficiency with TOSCA modules and Self-Healing features.</li>
      <li>Knowledge of DevOps, Agile, and CI/CD pipelines.</li>
      <li>Professional certifications like <a href="https://www.h2kinfosys.com/courses/tosca-automation-tool-training-and-certification-program/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">TOSCA Training</a>.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Career Outlook</h2>
    <p>
      TOSCA automation engineers are increasingly in demand due to the emphasis on quality and efficiency in software development. Mastering automation tools, keeping skills up-to-date, and obtaining certifications can significantly enhance employability and salary potential.
    </p>
  </section>

